      "content": "I hear how overwhelming this is, and it makes complete sense that you feel exhausted from fighting it all alone. When grief hits that hard, it can feel like the noise in your head is constant and the heaviness in your chest is permanent, making everything seem pointless. You don't have to make sense of it right now, and you don't have to be strong if you're not feeling it. Sometimes, just acknowledging that it's too much is enough to take the edge off for a little while. Would you be open to sharing one small thing that feels manageable right now, or perhaps just sitting with the feeling without trying to fix it?",
